    <p>
      This blog web application was created as an educational project to demonstrate the use of Node.js, Express.js and EJS for building full stack web applications. It allows users to create, view, edit and delete blog posts through a simple and responsive interface. Since it does not use a database, posts are not saved after a page refresh. The project focuses on practicing routing, form handling and server side rendering with an emphasis on clean design and user experience. Future improvements may include adding a database, authentication and search functionality.
    </p>
